Hi @otakueadwine!

It looks like you're using a custom theme. In that case, you'll need to add a background color to the `th` and if you're including borders, you'll need to add that to the inner block. I set up [this demo](https://jsfiddle.net/Mottie/f36416oy/46/) with the following custom css:

```css
table {
  width: 100%;
  border-collapsed: collapsed;
  border-spacing: 0;
}
table, td, caption {
  border: 1px solid #ddd;
  padding: 2px 4px;
}
th {
  padding: 0;
}
.tablesorter-header-inner {
  border: 1px solid #ddd;
  border-width: 0 1px 0 0;
  padding: 2px 4px;
}
.tablesorter-header-inner:first-child {
  border-left-width: 1px;
}
th, thead, caption {
  background: #eee;
}
```

Just in case anyone else can benefit from this, I wound up attaching my tags to a specific field instead of to a row.  Then I modified Mottie's example to:

```javascript
textExtraction: function(node, table, columnIndex)
{
	if ($(node).hasClass('tagged'))
	{
		return node.textContent + ' ' + $(node).attr('data-tags');
	}
	return node.textContent
},
```

@jamiebull1 I tried to filter out the required fields using the `objidd` field. But it has some contradictions.

For example, in **Energy+.idd** file, for the IDF object _Connector:Splitter_, the field name "Outlet Branch 1 Name" is only specified as required. But in the information returned by objidd field, all 500 are coming as required.

Similarly, _Table:TwoIndependentVariables_, _OutdoorAir:NodeList_ and few more IDF objects have such optional fields marked as required fields.

