@oxtopus, regarding
> Instead, if we need to update pip, setuptools, or wheel, we should update `get-pip.py`

We don't want to modify `get-pip.py`. Instead, since `get-pip.py` accepts all command-line options that you can pass to `pip`, we simply pass the required packages (pip, setuptools, wheel) along with their versions to `get-pip.py` using a script that is shared between the builds.

