@annatisch , CentOS 7 (Linux kernel 3.10.0-327.18.2.el7.x86_64). We're running under Python 3.5.1.

The order of operations we've been doing in (perhaps rapid succession?) is list_vms() a couple of times, then for each VM execute a get() to get the InstanceView. The entire cycle repeats at most once per minute. It's kind of random as to which get() call the hang occurs. Sometimes it's early in the process, sometimes later. Sometimes it can occur after an hour, sometimes after 12 hours.

Since then we've just stopped querying for the InstanceView and everything is working as expected. This deprives us of some useful data, but for the time being it's not too much of an issue. We were getting the PowerState out of the InstanceView since there's currently no way to see this when listing the VMs. I know multiple people have asked about seeing the PowerState in the list_vms() call; you can add me as another voice hoping for that feature or some equivalent at some point. :)

